## 3. Data Architecture

### In-Memory Database Object

The app maintains a single global `DB` object that is the in-memory working copy of all data:

```javascript
let DB = {
  customers:     [],   // Customer records
  sales:         [],   // Invoice/sale records
  payments:      [],   // Payment records
  items:         [],   // Product catalog items
  settings:      [],   // App settings (PIN hash, etc.)
  dispatch:      [],   // Daily dispatch records
  notifications: [],   // In-app alert log
  invoiceSeq:    1     // Auto-increment invoice counter
};
```

This object is saved to `localStorage` on every change via `saveDB()`, and synced to Firebase via `fbWrite()` / `fbRemove()`.

