## 9. Feature: Sales Invoices

### Invoice Entry Form

The invoice form (`page-invoice-form`) is a full-page section (not a floating modal) with:

**Sale Type Toggle (Dispatch / Shop)**
This is a sliding pill toggle — the most prominent feature of the entry form. It determines:
- **Dispatch** — goods went out on the van. Qty sold deducts from the daily dispatch balance for this item.
- **Shop** — sold from the retail store. Does NOT touch the dispatch balance.

The toggle has an animated sliding knob. Green for Dispatch, amber for Shop.

**Customer Selection**
Uses the reusable combo widget (`comboRender`, `comboOpen`, `comboSelect`) — a text input that searches customers live as you type, and shows a scrollable dropdown. Supports quick-add inline.

**Auto-fill for Cash Sale customer:**
When "Cash Sale" is selected, a note appears saying the sale will be recorded as paid in full immediately. The payment section pre-fills the total.

**Dynamic Line Items**
Multiple line items can be added. Each item row has:
- Description (text input with datalist autocomplete from the items catalog)
- Quantity
- Rate (price per unit, in AED)
- Row total (qty × rate, computed live)
- A delete button

Items in the datalist come from `DB.items` (the catalog). If a typed description matches a saved item, the rate auto-fills. A save button on each row lets users add new items to the catalog directly from the invoice.

**Item Normalization for Dispatch Matching**
Item names are matched case-insensitively and stripped of leading/trailing spaces via `normItemName()`. This is critical — `"Blade "` and `"blade"` must be treated as the same item for dispatch reconciliation.

**VAT Toggle**
A checkbox per invoice. When checked:
- Subtotal = sum of all item totals
- VAT 5% is calculated on the subtotal
- Invoice total = subtotal + VAT
- The invoice label changes to "Tax Invoice" and the company TRN appears

**Partial Payment on Invoice Save**
When saving an invoice, users can optionally record an immediate payment:
- Enter the amount paid now
- Select payment method (Cash, Bank Transfer, Cheque, Card)
- Balance due is shown live: `total − paidAmount`
- "Mark Fully Paid" button auto-fills the total as paid

When an invoice is saved with a partial or full payment, **a linked payment record is created automatically** (`fromSale: true, saleId: ...`). If the invoice is later edited and the paid amount changes, the linked payment is updated. If the paid amount becomes zero, the linked payment is deleted.

### Invoice Status Badges

Each invoice in the list shows a colored badge:
- **Paid** (green) — `paidAmount >= total`
- **Partial** (amber) — `0 < paidAmount < total`
- **Due** (red/grey) — `paidAmount = 0`

Plus a status badge computed from credit terms:
- **Overdue** — past due date with balance
- **Due Today** — due date is today

### Invoice Filters

The sales list supports simultaneous filtering by:
- Free text search (customer name, invoice number)
- Item description search
- Customer dropdown
- Date range (from / to)
- Quick date buttons: Today, Yesterday, 2 Days Ago, 3 Days Ago, This Week, This Month, Last Month, All Time
- Sale type: All / Dispatch / Shop
- Status: All / Overdue / Due Today

**Item Search Summary Panel**
When filtering by item description, a summary card appears above the invoice list showing: which customers bought that item, how many units each bought, and the total value — all within the selected date range.

### Invoice Auto-Numbering

Invoice numbers use a sequential counter (`DB.invoiceSeq`) stored in the database, generating numbers like `INV-001`, `INV-002`, etc. The counter increments on each new invoice and persists across sessions.

### Duplicate Detection

After every save, `checkDuplicateInvoice(sale)` checks if the same customer already has another invoice on the same date. If so, a notification is added to the in-app inbox. It never blocks saving — it only warns.

Exception: the Cash Sale customer is exempt, since multiple walk-in sales on the same day are normal.

### Invoice Delete with Linked Payment Cleanup

Deleting an invoice also deletes its linked payment (the one auto-created at the time of saving, tagged `fromSale: true`) via `deleteSale()`. This prevents orphaned payment records from inflating the "money collected" figures.

