## 22. Utility Functions & Core Logic

### `roundMoney(n)`

All monetary calculations route through this function:
```javascript
function roundMoney(n) {
  return Math.round((Number(n) || 0) * 100) / 100;
}
```

Plain JS floating point math (`0.1 + 0.2 = 0.30000000000000004`) can leave amounts a fraction of a fils off, which then silently mismatches later comparisons. All comparisons involving money use a 0.004 epsilon (`if (balance <= 0.004)`) to absorb rounding artifacts.

### `fmtMoney(n)`

Formats a number as AED currency with `toLocaleString`:
```javascript
'AED ' + n.toLocaleString('en-AE', { minimumFractionDigits: 2, maximumFractionDigits: 2 })
```

Uses `en-AE` locale so thousands separator and decimal format match UAE conventions.

### `fmtDate(d)`

Converts a `YYYY-MM-DD` string to human-readable `DD Mon YYYY` (e.g., `22 Jul 2025`). Uses `en-GB` locale to get the day-first format:
```javascript
new Date(d + 'T00:00:00').toLocaleDateString('en-GB', { day: '2-digit', month: 'short', year: 'numeric' })
```

The `T00:00:00` suffix is critical — without it, parsing a date string in ISO format is treated as UTC by the browser, which can shift the date by a day in non-UTC timezones.

### `escapeHtml(str)`

Prevents XSS injection when inserting user-entered text into `innerHTML`:
```javascript
String(str).replace(/[&<>"']/g, m => ({ '&': '&amp;', '<': '&lt;', '>': '&gt;', '"': '&quot;', "'": '&#39;' }[m]));
```

Used on every customer name, invoice number, item description, and note before it is inserted into any HTML.

### `custDisplayName(cust)`

Prefers Urdu name over English for all display purposes:
```javascript
return (cust.nameUr && cust.nameUr.trim()) ? cust.nameUr.trim() : cust.nameEn;
```

### `toast(msg, type)`

Shows a non-blocking notification chip in the top-right corner:
- Default: dark navy background (info/success)
- `type='err'`: red background

Toasts appear with a slide-in animation and auto-dismiss after 2.6 seconds.

### Date Range Logic (`getDateRange`)

Powers the quick range buttons across all list pages. Accepts:
- `'today'`, `'thismonth'`, `'lastmonth'`, `'all'`
- Or a numeric offset (1 = yesterday, 2 = 2 days ago, etc.)

Returns `{ from: 'YYYY-MM-DD', to: 'YYYY-MM-DD' }`.

### `setSalesRange` / `setPaymentsRange`

Set the date filters on the Sales / Payments pages respectively. Called on app init with `'today'` so the pages always open showing today's data rather than all-time data.

