## 23. Security Considerations

### What is Protected
- All business data is in localStorage and Firebase
- The PIN prevents unauthorized access via the browser
- Wrong PINs are logged and notified

### What is Not Protected
- The Firebase API key is embedded in the HTML. This is normal for client-side Firebase apps; Firebase security should be enforced via Database Rules on the Firebase console, not by hiding the key.
- Anyone who opens the raw HTML file on the same device (where localStorage is shared) can see data without Firebase — the PIN protects the UI but not the raw localStorage data.
- The PIN hash is SHA-256, which is not bcrypt — for a business app this is acceptable, but a dedicated secrets manager would be stronger.

### XSS Prevention
All user-input values are escaped via `escapeHtml()` before `innerHTML` insertion. This prevents any customer name, invoice note, or item description from being interpreted as HTML/JavaScript.

